PEOPLE: LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
* Richard A. Gilleland, 44, has been elected chairman of American Medical 
International, the Beverly Hills-based hospital chain. He previously had 
assumed the duties of chief executive. Gilleland was formerly chairman of 
Intermedics, an Angleton, Tex.-based producer of cardiac pacemakers and other 
biomedical devices. Gilleland succeeded Royce Diener, who had assumed the 
position of chairman and chief executive on an interim basis after AMI's board 
forced Walter L. Weisman to resign Aug. 30. 
